{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1173","heading":"Formal evaluation of recommendations","label":"1173 Formal evaluation of recommendations","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/ptII/ch11/schVII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Formal Evaluations","label":"a .—Formal Evaluations","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall establish a process to conduct a formal evaluation with respect to each recommendation made by the Working Group under .section 1172 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Evidence, Data, and Factors","label":"b .—Evidence, Data, and Factors","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Scientific evidence, based on the review of available scientific literature, including human, toxicological, animal, and methodological studies, and other factors.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Claims data, based on the review of claim rate, grant rate, and service connection prevalence, and other factors.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the level of disability and mortality caused by the health effects related to the case of toxic exposure being evaluated;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the quantity and quality of the information available and reviewed;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the feasibility of and period for generating relevant information and evidence;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb%2F3%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"whether such health effects are combat- or deployment-related;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb%2F3%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the ubiquity or rarity of the health effects; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fb%2F3%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any time frame during which a health effect must become manifest.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Conduct of Evaluations","label":"c .—Conduct of Evaluations","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"conforms to principles of scientific and data integrity;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is free from suppression or distortion of scientific or technological findings, data, information, conclusions, or technical results; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"evaluates the likelihood that a positive association exists between an illness and a toxic exposure while serving in the active military, naval, air, or space service; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"assesses the toxic exposures and illnesses and determines whether the evidence supports a finding of a positive association between the toxic exposure and the illness.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The “sufficient” category, where the evidence is sufficient to conclude that a positive association exists.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The “equipoise and above” category, where the evidence is sufficient to conclude that a positive association is at least as likely as not, but not sufficient to conclude that a positive association exists.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The “below equipoise” category, where the evidence is not sufficient to conclude that a positive association is at least as likely as not, or is not sufficient to make a scientifically informed judgment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fc%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The “against” category, where the evidence suggests the lack of a positive association.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Recommendation for Establishing a Presumption of Service Connection","label":"d .—Recommendation for Establishing a Presumption of Service Connection","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1173","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1173%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 120 days after the date on which a formal evaluation is commenced, the element of the Department that conducts the evaluation shall submit to the Secretary a recommendation with respect to establishing a presumption of service connection for the toxic exposure and illness, or modifying an existing presumption of service connection, covered by the evaluation.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
